===Reception===
Critics on Rotten Tomatoes gave ''Thor'' generally positive ratings with a 77% fresh certified fresh and an average rating of 6.7/10. The consensus called the film, "A dazzling blockbuster that tempers its sweeping scope with wit, humor, and human drama, Thor is mighty Marvel entertainment."<ref>{{Rotten-tomatoes|id=thor}}</ref> However, top critics on Metacritic gave the film mixed or average reviews with a normalized score of 58/100.<ref>[http://www.metacritic.com/movie/thor ''Thor''] on Metacritic </ref> Richard Roeper of the Chicago Sun-Times praised the film, calling it "the most entertaining superhero debut since the original {{sl|Spider-Man (2002 film)}}," attributing its success to Chris Hemsworth performance as Thor.<ref>[http://www.richardroeper.com/reviews/thor.aspx ''Thor'' Review] on RichardRoeper.com</ref> On the other hand, Roger Ebert, also of the Chicago Sun-Times, gave the film a negative review, calling the screenplay a failure and found the characters uninteresting.<ref>[http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20110510/REVIEWS/110519987 Thor :: rogerebert.com :: Reviews] on the SunTimes.com. May 10, 2011.</ref>
